caption: Table 1: Comparison of weight initialization methods trained on pretrained from epochs 21–25. We compare: (1) training from scratch (tr. fr. scratch), (2) SKDE30subscript𝑆KDE30S_{\mathrm{KDE30}}italic_S start_POSTSUBSCRIPT KDE30 end_POSTSUBSCRIPT (Schürholt et al., 2022b), (3) SANE with K⁢D⁢E⁢30𝐾𝐷𝐸30KDE30italic_K italic_D italic_E 30, (4) subsampled SANESUB (aligned with IGPG), and (5) D2NWG (Soro et al., 2024).
description: This table compares the performance of several weight initialization methods on four benchmark datasets (MNIST, SVHN, CIFAR-10, STL).  The methods include training a model from scratch, and four different pre-trained weight initialization techniques: SKDE30 (Schürholt et al., 2022b), SANE with KDE30, a subsampled version of SANE (aligned with the proposed method IGPG), and D2NWG (Soro et al., 2024). The results show the top-1 and top-5 accuracies achieved by each method on each dataset after training for a specified number of epochs (21-25).  The goal is to demonstrate how the proposed IGPG method compares to existing state-of-the-art techniques in terms of weight initialization performance.

description: This table presents a comparison of model performance using different methods for generating neural network weights.  It uses two model architectures, ViT-Small and MobileNetV3-Small, trained on a diverse set of image datasets (CIFAR-10, CIFAR-100, CINIC-10, SVHN, Tiny-ImageNet, and ImageNet). For each model and dataset combination, it shows the model's size (in parameters), the pretrained accuracy (the accuracy before any weight modifications), the VQVAE reconstruction accuracy (the accuracy after encoding and decoding the pretrained weights using a Vector Quantized Variational Autoencoder), and the best sampled weights accuracy (the accuracy of the best performing model from five randomly sampled models generated by the proposed method, IGPG). This allows for an evaluation of the effectiveness of the proposed IGPG method in preserving model accuracy while potentially improving it.
